<Heading Level="HeadingLevel.H2">Media Component</Heading>
<Paragraph>
    The <Anchor Url="https://getbootstrap.com/docs/4.5/components/media-object/" OpenInNewTab="true">Media component</Anchor> is used to build complex and repetitive content where media is positioned alongside content.
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph>
    The media objects below have all a border to better visualize the layout. They also use a padding to add some distance between the border and the contents of the media object. Neither
    border nor padding are by default added to the media object, but you can add them using the <code>BorderColor</code> and <code>Padding</code> parameters.
</Paragraph>

<DocsSection ComponentName="Media" />



<Heading Id="basic" IsAnchor="true" Level="HeadingLevel.H3" MarginTop="@headingMarginTop">Basic Media objects</Heading>
<Paragraph>
    An example of a single media object as it is rendered by default.
</Paragraph>
<Media Heading="Standard Media Object" ImageUrl="@this.ImageUrl" BorderColor="NamedColor.Black50" Padding="3">
    <Paragraph>
        This is a standard Bootstrap media object using the default settings and minimal markup.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        The rest of this text is here to demonstrate how the vertical alignment of the image is set by default.
        The image should be top-aligned on the left when this text wraps to multiple lines.
    </Paragraph>
</Media>



<Heading Id="nesting" IsAnchor="true" Level="HeadingLevel.H3" MarginTop="@headingMarginTop">Nesting Objects</Heading>
<Paragraph>
    The example below shows you how you can nest media objects inside oneanother.
</Paragraph>
<Media Heading="Standard Media Object" ImageUrl="@this.ImageUrl" BorderColor="NamedColor.Black50" Padding="3">
    <Paragraph>
        This is the root media object with nested objects inside of it.
    </Paragraph>
    <Media Heading="Child Media Object" ImageUrl="@this.ImageUrl" BorderColor="NamedColor.Black50" Padding="3">
        <Paragraph>
            This media object is nested inside of another media object.
        </Paragraph>
        <Media Heading="Grandchild Media Object" ImageUrl="@this.ImageUrl" BorderColor="NamedColor.Black50" Padding="3">
            <Paragraph>
                Yet another nested media object.
            </Paragraph>
        </Media>
    </Media>
</Media>



<Heading Id="vertical-alignment" IsAnchor="true" Level="HeadingLevel.H3" MarginTop="@headingMarginTop">Vertical Alignment</Heading>
<Paragraph>
    The samples below shown you how you can align the media vertically.
</Paragraph>
<Media Heading="Top Aligned Media" ImageUrl="@this.ImageUrl" ImageVerticalAlignment="VerticalAlignment.Top" BorderColor="NamedColor.Black50" Padding="3">
    <Paragraph MarginBottom="5">
        This media object has its media aligned to the top.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph MarginTop="5">
        The rest of this text is here just to fill up some space so that the alignment is visible.
    </Paragraph>
</Media>
<Media Heading="Middle Aligned Media" ImageUrl="@this.ImageUrl" ImageVerticalAlignment="VerticalAlignment.Middle" BorderColor="NamedColor.Black50" Padding="3">
    <Paragraph MarginBottom="5">
        This media object has its media aligned to the middle.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph MarginTop="5">
        The rest of this text is here just to fill up some space so that the alignment is visible.
    </Paragraph>
</Media>
<Media Heading="Bottom Aligned Media" ImageUrl="@this.ImageUrl" ImageVerticalAlignment="VerticalAlignment.Bottom" BorderColor="NamedColor.Black50" Padding="3">
    <Paragraph MarginBottom="5">
        This media object has its media aligned to the bottom.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph MarginTop="5">
        The rest of this text is here just to fill up some space so that the alignment is visible.
    </Paragraph>
</Media>



<Heading Id="horizontal-alignment" IsAnchor="true" Level="HeadingLevel.H3" MarginTop="@headingMarginTop">Horizontal Alignment</Heading>
<Paragraph>
    The examples below shows you how you can align the media either to the left (default) or to the right.
</Paragraph>

<Media Heading="Left-Aligned Media" ImageUrl="@this.ImageUrl" BorderColor="NamedColor.Black50" Padding="3">
    <Paragraph>
        The media is aligned to the left of this text. This is also the default behaviour, if you don't specify the horizontal alignment.
    </Paragraph>
</Media>

<Media Heading="Right-Aligned Media" ImageUrl="@this.ImageUrl" ImageHorizontalAlignment="HorizontalAlignment.Right" BorderColor="NamedColor.Black50" Padding="3">
    <Paragraph>
        The media is aligned to the right of this text. This is done by specifying <code>HorizontalAlignment.Right</code>
        on the <code>ImageHorizontalAlignment</code> parameter.
    </Paragraph>
</Media>